   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_196281_1829_05_11_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/>Edgeworths Town
                  <date when="1829-11-05">May 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>, 1829.</date>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>The bearer, <persName ref="./Personography.xml#McLaJ1">John M<hi rend="superscript">c</hi>Laughlin</persName> has<lb/>
               been employed by the Edgeworth family<lb/>
               as a laborer for many years-- He is<lb/>
               a good groom -- a <hi rend="underline">very</hi> good groom -- He is<lb/> 
               honest, industrious, and for the<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">last four years sober as our our steward assures me</hi>
               <lb/>
               We have had many opportunities<lb/>
               of judging of his honesty, because he<lb/>
               he has been trusted in every room in<lb/>
               this house when it was painting &amp;<lb/>
               when he had no watch over him<lb/>
               but his own honesty - Nothing was<lb/>
               ever missed - At another time when<lb/>
               this house was on fire he distinguished<lb/>
               himself by his zeal, courage &amp; presence<lb/>
               of mind -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>His fellow workmen are all<lb/>
               sorry he is going away; We all wish<lb/>
               that he may improve his own condition<lb/>
               by going to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#US">America</placeName> &amp; in this hope I give<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_196281_1829_05_11_page02.jpg"/>

               him this character- which I trust may<lb/>
               procure him employment as I am<lb/>
               told has been the consequence of some<lb/>
               characters which have been given by me<lb/>
               to persons going to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#US">America</placeName> - <add>This I chiefly attribute to</add> my never<lb/>
               putting my name to any <choice>
                  <orig>recommen-<lb/>
               dation</orig>
                  <reg>recommendation</reg>
               </choice>
               <del>which</del> but what I seriously<lb/>
               believe to be true &amp; just -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <date when="1829-05-11">May 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1829</date><lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_196281_1829_05_11_page03.jpg"/>
               <note>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>'s letter<lb/>
               recommending <persName ref="./Personography.xml#McLaJ1">John <choice>
                        <orig>M<hi rend="superscript">c</hi>Glaughlin</orig>
                        <reg>M<hi rend="superscript">c</hi>Laughlin</reg>
                     </choice>
                  </persName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthtown Ireland</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1829-05-11">May 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1829</date> </note>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
